parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the steering wheel locks up
the power steering fluid level is low
the vehicle is difficult to maneuver at low speeds
and the power steering pump or rack and pinion may need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall or shut off, leading to a loss of power steering and brakes, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off
the vehicle loses power steering and brakes
the timing chain needs to be replaced
and the engine may need to be repaired or replaced.
